3. d4 {[%cal Bd4d5,Bd4e5][%csl Be5,Bd5]} d5 {[%cal Bf3e5][%csl Be5]} { Don't let this strange looking move throw you off. The following line is the simplest way to walk away with a great position. } 
4. Nxe5 dxe4 
5. Bb5 {[%cal Bb5c6,Be5c6][%csl Bc6]} { White is immediately putting pressure on the c6-knight and threatening the d5 advance. } Bd7 
6. Nxd7 Qxd7 
