8. dxc6 Qxd1+ 
9. Kxd1 O-O-O+ {[%cal Bd8d1][%csl Bd1]} { Black gets a chance to improve their position by castling queenside with a tempo on White's king. } 
10. Ke2 axb5 
11. cxb7+ {[%cal Bb1c3,Bc1f4,Bh1d1][%csl Bc3,Bf4,Bd1]} { Again, White has a healthy +1 positional advantage with a three vs two queenside pawn majority. Black's pawns on b5 and e4 look out of place and are fantastic targets for our developing pieces. } *

